---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
import Markdown from '../../../Markdown.astro';
import AIBalloon from '../../AIBalloon.astro';
import AIBalloonMessage from '../../AIBalloonMessage.astro';
import AIResponseFollowUp from '../../AIResponseFollowUp.astro';
import AIResponseFollowUpAction from '../../AIResponseFollowUpAction.astro';
import AIResponseMessage from '../../AIResponseMessage.astro';
import Highlight from '../../Highlight.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Language and Explanation Adaptation"
  description="Match terminology and explanation depth to the user's expertiseâ€”plain language for general users, precise terms and more detail for experts when appropriate."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={328} label="Progressive disclosure" multiple>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <!-- <mds-badge variant="warning" tone="weak" class="justify-self-center">Novice</mds-badge> -->
      <Highlight label="Novice speech detection">
        <AIBalloon>
          <AIBalloonMessage>How can I start feeding birds in my garden?</AIBalloonMessage>
        </AIBalloon>
      </Highlight>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <Markdown
          typography="detail"
          content={`
To start feeding your baby birds, just follow a few simple steps:

1. **Choose a basic feed:** Use sunflower
2. **Position the feeder:** Hang it in a sheltered
3. **Clean regularly:** Remove old or wet seeds to prevent mold.

Want to know which birds you can attract or how to protect
your food from rain?
      `}
        />
        <!-- <AIResponseFollowUp>
          <AIResponseFollowUpAction>
            Find out which birds you might attract
          </AIResponseFollowUpAction>
          <AIResponseFollowUpAction>
            Watch a video on how to hang the feeder
          </AIResponseFollowUpAction>
          <AIResponseFollowUpAction>Buy recommended seeds</AIResponseFollowUpAction>
        </AIResponseFollowUp> -->
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <Highlight label="Expert speech detection">
        <AIBalloon>
          <AIBalloonMessage>
            What seed mixes are best for attracting finches and tits in winter, considering the
            presence of cats?
          </AIBalloonMessage>
        </AIBalloon>
      </Highlight>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <Markdown
          typography="detail"
          content={`
For finches and tits in winter, where cats are present, I recommend:

1. **Leftover mix:** Black sunflower seeds (rich in oil), niger (for finches), and unsalted peanuts (for tits).
2. **Strategic placement:** Use a tube feeder with small holes (for finches) or a cage-style feeder (for tits), hung at least 1.8 meters high and away from branches where cats can climb.
3. **Additional protection:** Add a baffle (plastic disc) over the feeder to deter cats.

Want to learn more about managing seed cleaning in humid environments or how to incorporate nuts into their diet?
      `}
        />
        <AIResponseFollowUp>
          <AIResponseFollowUpAction>
            Download the PDF guide on anti-predator feeders
          </AIResponseFollowUpAction>
          <AIResponseFollowUpAction>
            Calculate the amount of seeds for the season
          </AIResponseFollowUpAction>
          <AIResponseFollowUpAction>Set up a monthly cleaning reminder</AIResponseFollowUpAction>
        </AIResponseFollowUp>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Use plain language by default; offer detailed or technical explanations when users need them.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Use technical jargon or dense explanations for all users regardless of expertise.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Let users switch explanation depth (simple vs detailed) in settings or per interaction.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Force one level of explanation with no way to get simpler or more detailed content.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
